{
    "id": "auxiliary-verbs-h",
    "title": "Auxiliary Verbs (सहायक क्रियाएँ)",
    "description": "Auxiliary Verbs (सहायक क्रियाएँ) वे क्रियाएँ हैं जो मुख्य क्रिया (Main Verb) को काल (Tense), भाव (Mood) और वाक्य का प्रकार बनाने में मदद करती हैं।",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "Auxiliary Verbs के प्रकार"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "<b>Primary Auxiliaries:</b> Be, Have, Do (जो मुख्य क्रिया के रूप में भी उपयोग होती हैं).",
                "<b>Modal Auxiliaries:</b> Can, Could, May, Might, Shall, Should, Must, आदि (जो केवल भाव दर्शाने के लिए उपयोग होती हैं)."
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "1. Primary Auxiliaries (Be, Have, Do)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "ये क्रियाएँ काल (Tenses), प्रश्नवाचक वाक्य और नकार वाक्य बनाने में मदद करती हैं।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Uses & Examples",
                        "headers": [
                            "Verb Forms",
                            "Use",
                            "Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "<b>To Be</b><br>(am, is, are, was, were)",
                                "Continuous Tense & Passive Voice",
                                "She <b>is</b> writing.<br>The car <b>was</b> sold."
                            ],
                            [
                                "<b>To Have</b><br>(has, have, had)",
                                "Perfect Tenses",
                                "I <b>have</b> finished my work.<br>He <b>had</b> gone."
                            ],
                            [
                                "<b>To Do</b><br>(do, does, did)",
                                "Questions & Negatives (Simple Tense)",
                                "<b>Do</b> you play?<br>She <b>does not</b> know."
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "note",
                    "content": "<b>To be + Infinitive:</b> पूर्व नियोजित योजना के लिए।<br>Example: I <b>am to go</b> to Mumbai tomorrow. (मुझे कल मुंबई जाना है।)"
                },
                {
                    "type": "note",
                    "content": "<b>Have to + V1:</b> अनिवार्यता (Compulsion) दर्शाने के लिए।<br>Example: I <b>have to finish</b> this today. (मुझे यह आज खत्म करना है।)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "2. Can vs Could",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "<b>Can:</b> शक्ति, सामर्थ्य (वर्तमान), अनुमति।<br><b>Could:</b> शक्ति (भूतकाल), विनम्र निवेदन, संभावना।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Comparison",
                        "headers": [
                            "Usage",
                            "Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "Ability (Present)",
                                "I <b>can</b> lift this box."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Ability (Past)",
                                "I <b>could</b> run fast when I was young."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Polite Request",
                                "<b>Could</b> you please help me? (Can से अधिक विनम्र)"
                            ],
                            [
                                "Past Possibility (Could have + V3)",
                                "He <b>could have won</b> the match (but he didn't)."
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "3. May vs Might",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "<b>May:</b> अधिक संभावना, अनुमति, शुभकामना।<br><b>Might:</b> कम संभावना, May का भूतकाल।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Comparison",
                        "headers": [
                            "Usage",
                            "Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "Permission",
                                "<b>May</b> I come in, Sir?"
                            ],
                            [
                                "Possibility (Strong)",
                                "It <b>may</b> rain today. (बादल हैं)"
                            ],
                            [
                                "Possibility (Weak)",
                                "It <b>might</b> rain today. (आसमान साफ है)"
                            ],
                            [
                                "Wish / Prayer",
                                "<b>May</b> God bless you!"
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "4. Will vs Would",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "<b>Will:</b> भविष्यकाल, निश्चय, वादा।<br><b>Would:</b> भूतकाल की आदत, निवेदन, पसंद।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Uses",
                        "headers": [
                            "Usage",
                            "Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "Future / Promise",
                                "I <b>will</b> help you."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Past Habit",
                                "He <b>would</b> sit here for hours."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Polite Offer/Request",
                                "<b>Would</b> you like some tea?"
                            ],
                            [
                                "Preference (Would rather)",
                                "I <b>would rather</b> die than beg. (मैं भीख मांगने की बजाय मरना पसंद करूँगा।)"
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "5. Should, Ought to & Must",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "<b>Should:</b> सलाह, कर्तव्य।<br><b>Ought to:</b> नैतिक कर्तव्य।<br><b>Must:</b> अनिवार्यता, मजबूरी।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Differences",
                        "headers": [
                            "Usage",
                            "Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "Advice / Duty (Should)",
                                "You <b>should</b> work hard."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Moral Duty (Ought to)",
                                "We <b>ought to</b> respect elders."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Compulsion (Must)",
                                "You <b>must</b> follow the rules."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Purpose (Lest... Should)",
                                "Work hard <b>lest</b> you <b>should</b> fail. (कहीं ऐसा न हो कि तुम फेल हो जाओ।)"
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "6. Special Auxiliaries (Need, Dare, Used to)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Rules",
                        "headers": [
                            "Verb",
                            "Usage & Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "<b>Need</b> (आवश्यकता होना)",
                                "Active: He <b>needs</b> to go.<br>Negative (Modal): He <b>need not</b> go."
                            ],
                            [
                                "<b>Dare</b> (हिम्मत होना)",
                                "How <b>dare</b> you speak like this?<br>He <b>dare not</b> oppose me."
                            ],
                            [
                                "<b>Used to</b> (भूतकाल की आदत)",
                                "I <b>used to</b> play cricket in childhood."
                            ],
                            [
                                "<b>Had better</b> (सलाह)",
                                "You <b>had better</b> consult a doctor. (तुम्हारे लिए डॉक्टर को दिखाना बेहतर होगा।)"
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}